Yes, sir.

259
00:25:06,502 --> 00:25:07,708
Velez?

260
00:25:09,038 --> 00:25:10,711
Velez?

261
00:25:10,773 --> 00:25:12,081
I'm good!

262
00:25:13,444 --> 00:25:14,889
Let's go, fellas.

263
00:25:32,131 --> 00:25:34,236
Incoming!
Grenade!

264
00:25:51,252 --> 00:25:52,788
Greer!

265
00:25:53,921 --> 00:25:56,231
Step-slide!
Start walking back!

266
00:26:00,262 --> 00:26:01,798
Velez!
Three-round bursts!

267
00:26:14,210 --> 00:26:15,814
Velez, where's Greer?

268
00:26:15,880 --> 00:26:17,120
He's over there, sir.

269
00:26:17,815 --> 00:26:18,816
Go, son.

270
00:26:28,226 --> 00:26:30,638
This ain't a test.
This is the real thing.

271
00:26:34,901 --> 00:26:35,902
What are you
gonna do?

272
00:26:36,469 --> 00:26:37,539
You don't want
to try me.

273
00:26:45,445 --> 00:26:47,220
Magazine!
Let's go.

274
00:26:53,221 --> 00:26:55,167
Velez, stay there!

275
00:26:55,723 --> 00:26:57,168
Listen to me
stay there!

276
00:27:02,798 --> 00:27:03,799
Son of a bitch!

277
00:27:12,209 --> 00:27:13,210
Miller!

278
00:27:16,213 --> 00:27:17,214
Miller!

279
00:27:18,682 --> 00:27:20,127
Hey! Get in here!

280
00:27:23,154 --> 00:27:24,929
Hey, hey. Take these.

281
00:27:24,989 --> 00:27:26,400
Go watch him.

282
00:27:42,175 --> 00:27:45,054
Hey, they're here for me,
but they want me alive.

283
00:27:45,111 --> 00:27:46,215
You, they'll kill.

284
00:27:51,085 --> 00:27:52,120
You got one
in the chamber?

285
00:27:56,091 --> 00:27:57,399
It's okay.

286
00:27:58,126 --> 00:28:01,335
I remember my first posting.
Rio de Janeiro.

287
00:28:01,396 --> 00:28:04,070
A house like this.
Beautiful women.

288
00:28:04,132 --> 00:28:06,578
Not one single visitor, but
I remember rule number one.

289
00:28:06,636 --> 00:28:08,673
You are responsible
for your houseguest.

290
00:28:08,738 --> 00:28:09,739
I'm your houseguest.

291
00:28:14,878 --> 00:28:18,587
The clock is ticking.
They gave you the keys.

292
00:28:18,649 --> 00:28:19,719
Do your duty, son.

293
00:28:19,983 --> 00:28:22,429
Shut up. Let me think.

294
00:28:26,724 --> 00:28:28,533
You want to be the guy
that lost Tobin Frost?

295
00:28:34,033 --> 00:28:36,639
Tick-took,
tick-took, tick-took.

296
00:29:00,295 --> 00:29:02,036
Where's Frost?

297
00:29:25,824 --> 00:29:27,303
We're leaving.

298
00:29:44,911 --> 00:29:46,219
Where is he?

299
00:30:04,633 --> 00:30:06,874
Stay here, stay here!
Wait! Don't move!

300
00:30:10,572 --> 00:30:11,573
Hey, hey, hey!

301
00:30:18,114 --> 00:30:19,115
Go!

302
00:30:22,686 --> 00:30:23,687
Get in the trunk.

303
00:30:23,754 --> 00:30:25,791
Are you serious?
Yeah, get in.

304
00:30:25,856 --> 00:30:27,767
The trunk?
Get in the trunk now!

305
00:30:49,950 --> 00:30:50,951
No!

306
00:31:09,972 --> 00:31:10,973
Ops Center.

307
00:31:11,040 --> 00:31:13,247
Echo Three
Victor Echo Nine.

308
00:31:13,309 --> 00:31:14,310
Go ahead.

309
00:31:14,376 --> 00:31:16,754
This is Weston. 7-R's been hit.
Everyone's dead.

310
00:31:17,347 --> 00:31:19,088
I need you to repeat that, please.
Say again.

311
00:31:19,149 --> 00:31:22,289
Kiefer, his team, everyone,
they're all dead.

312
00:31:22,352 --> 00:31:23,626
Stand by.

313
00:31:25,756 --> 00:31:26,757
Transferring.

314
00:31:27,758 --> 00:31:29,863
It's the house.

315
00:31:31,395 --> 00:31:33,033
Linklater.
This is Weston.

316
00:31:33,098 --> 00:31:34,577
The safe house
has been breached.

317
00:31:36,201 --> 00:31:37,407
What's your location?

318
00:31:37,569 --> 00:31:39,515
I'm eastbound
on Albert Road.

319
00:31:39,571 --> 00:31:42,074
I'm just
passing Woodstock.

320
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:45,881
I want eyes on this.
Real-time sat feed.

321
00:31:46,346 --> 00:31:48,849
And what's
the location of the guest?

322
00:31:49,115 --> 00:31:50,458
We escaped.

323
00:31:50,517 --> 00:31:52,190
Clarify.
Do you have the guest?

324
00:31:52,386 --> 00:31:53,558
Yes, we escaped!

325
00:31:54,388 --> 00:31:55,992
Look, I can make it
to the consulate.

326
00:31:56,056 --> 00:31:57,330
There's no chance
for SDR,

327
00:31:57,391 --> 00:31:58,631
I think I might have
picked up a tail.

328
00:31:59,059 --> 00:32:00,902
We can't have a gun battle
in front of the consulate.

329
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:03,473
Diplomatic catastrophe.

330
00:32:03,765 --> 00:32:05,267
Where's that
satellite feed?

331
00:32:05,333 --> 00:32:07,472
Denied by National Recon
War theater use only.

332
00:32:08,436 --> 00:32:10,143
Buy us some time.

333
00:32:13,042 --> 00:32:14,248
Do not go
to the consulate.

334
00:32:14,911 --> 00:32:16,857
Follow protocol
Alpha Zero.

335
00:32:17,180 --> 00:32:19,558
Secure the guest
and stay off the grid.

336
00:32:19,883 --> 00:32:23,797
Reconnect at 1800 hours.
I repeat, stay off the grid.

337
00:32:24,388 --> 00:32:26,061
Copy. copy. copy.

338
00:35:38,237 --> 00:35:40,114
All right, Cape Town police
have responded to the house.

339
00:35:40,172 --> 00:35:41,412
Confirmed.
I want the site secured.

340
00:35:41,473 --> 00:35:42,474
I'm hearing nine dead.

341
00:35:42,975 --> 00:35:44,181
Initiating damage control.

342
00:35:44,309 --> 00:35:46,016
I'm on it.
Reaching out to NIA now.

343
00:35:46,846 --> 00:35:49,053
The locals are going to
have that house locked off.

344
00:35:50,016 --> 00:35:53,088
Check all the traffic
cameras, police reports...

345
00:35:53,620 --> 00:35:56,829
Find out why Frost wanted to go
in that consulate to begin with

346
00:35:56,891 --> 00:35:58,461
and who in the hell else
might be after him.

347
00:36:00,795 --> 00:36:03,401
We need to get Weston and
Frost out of South Africa.

348
00:36:03,497 --> 00:36:06,239
Now, do we have any tactical teams?
Anything in play?

349
00:36:06,301 --> 00:36:08,713
Yeah, I have assets in
Egypt, but they're in deep.

350
00:36:08,770 --> 00:36:11,114
If I pull them out, that would
compromise two years' worth of work.

351
00:36:11,173 --> 00:36:12,743
I can scramble a team
from Europe or Asia,

352
00:36:12,808 --> 00:36:15,015
but it's going to
take at least 18 hours.

353
00:36:16,479 --> 00:36:19,221
At this point,
Weston is all we got.

354
00:36:22,853 --> 00:36:26,198
I need to find out who this
Matt Weston is, right now.

355
00:36:27,958 --> 00:36:29,335
Matthew James Weston.

356
00:36:30,194 --> 00:36:33,334
Born 02-24-82 to
Terry and Madeline Weston

357
00:36:33,398 --> 00:36:35,241
in Port Washington,
New York.

358
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:36,640
An assault arrest,
one month after

359
00:36:36,701 --> 00:36:37,771
both parents and
a younger sister

360
00:36:37,836 --> 00:36:39,509
were killed in
a traffic accident

361
00:36:39,571 --> 00:36:41,175
in which his
father's blood-alcohol

362
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,947
was twice
the legal limit.

363
00:36:43,242 --> 00:36:46,621
Yale, degree in Economics,
recruited out of Yale law.

364
00:36:46,946 --> 00:36:49,927
High marks in analytics
and linguistics at The Farm.

365
00:36:50,116 --> 00:36:52,494
Excellent in
tradecraft skills.

366
00:36:52,552 --> 00:36:55,624
His girlfriend, Ana Moreau,
is a French national.

367
00:36:56,389 --> 00:36:59,859
He reported them as having
"close and continuing contact. "

368
00:36:59,927 --> 00:37:02,806
She's a second year resident in the
oncology department at Groote Schuur.

369
00:37:02,864 --> 00:37:03,865
Get in that car.

370
00:37:03,931 --> 00:37:06,070
She accepted a
position with Hotel-Dieu Hospital

371
00:37:06,133 --> 00:37:07,806
in Paris,
starts in two weeks.

372
00:37:08,203 --> 00:37:10,581
No known political
affiliations. She's clean.

373
00:37:11,340 --> 00:37:13,251
I want you to post a car
outside their apartment.

374
00:37:13,308 --> 00:37:14,810
Use back channels.

375
00:37:14,877 --> 00:37:18,689
And get NSA to cross-check their telephone
records and their e-mails, please.

376
00:37:18,748 --> 00:37:19,749
Yes, ma'am.

377
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:35,076
You know, it would be easier
if I knew where we were going.

378
00:37:35,133 --> 00:37:38,307
You just drive, all right?
Just drive, middle lane.

379
00:37:38,370 --> 00:37:39,542
All right.

380
00:37:40,972 --> 00:37:43,714
Hey, what are you doing?
Middle lane.

381
00:37:45,811 --> 00:37:46,846
Just drive around.

382
00:37:46,913 --> 00:37:49,052
All right.
I'm driving.

383
00:37:53,620 --> 00:37:55,622
Nice to know who you're talking to.
What's your name?

384
00:37:56,657 --> 00:37:57,931
You crushed my windpipe.

385
00:37:57,991 --> 00:37:59,993
Well, you locked me
in the trunk.

386
00:38:03,264 --> 00:38:05,540
Come on, you're not NOC. You're
here under your real name.

387
00:38:05,600 --> 00:38:06,601
What is it?

388
00:38:06,668 --> 00:38:07,806
Weston, Matt.

389
00:38:07,869 --> 00:38:09,507
All right.

390
00:38:09,571 --> 00:38:11,380
How long you been
a safe house keeper?

391
00:38:11,440 --> 00:38:12,441
Twelve months.

392
00:38:12,508 --> 00:38:13,646
Happy birthday.

393
00:38:16,378 --> 00:38:18,324
Cape Town,
that's low-level detail.

394
00:38:18,380 --> 00:38:21,054
You should have been
out of here by now.

395
00:38:21,284 --> 00:38:23,230
Maybe I requested
the assignment.

396
00:38:24,454 --> 00:38:27,901
Or maybe Langley doesn't trust
you with anything else.

397
00:38:30,795 --> 00:38:32,433
So, what's your plan?

398
00:38:33,664 --> 00:38:35,541
Oh, let me guess.
Follow protocol.

399
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:37,773
Protocol states that
if your house is crashed,

400
00:38:37,835 --> 00:38:40,645
you do an SDR to make sure
no one's following you.

401
00:38:41,073 --> 00:38:44,953
Activate your GPS in your Go-Bag,
select another safe house.

402
00:38:46,712 --> 00:38:49,056
You think I'm going to
let you just take me in?

403
00:38:49,349 --> 00:38:50,623
I think you need
to shut up.

404
00:38:51,818 --> 00:38:54,526
I think you need to consider how your
house was attacked in the first place.

405
00:38:54,587 --> 00:38:56,589
Have you done that, Matt?

406
00:38:59,760 --> 00:39:02,172
They followed Kiefer. They
followed him from the consulate,

407
00:39:02,229 --> 00:39:03,333
and that's how they
found the safe house.

408
00:39:03,397 --> 00:39:05,035
Come on, you don't really
believe that, do you?

409
00:39:05,099 --> 00:39:08,603
How did they know I was near the
consulate in the first place?

410
00:39:10,805 --> 00:39:11,943
Hmm.

411
00:39:12,641 --> 00:39:15,349
But I like this, you know.
You and me, figuring shit out.

412
00:39:16,212 --> 00:39:18,351
Like the Hardy Boys.

413
00:39:20,449 --> 00:39:22,486
That house was
a secure location.

414
00:39:22,551 --> 00:39:23,928
Whoever crashed it

415
00:39:23,987 --> 00:39:28,163
didn't stop by a gas station and ask for
directions to the nearest safe house.

416
00:39:28,225 --> 00:39:30,535
They were invited. Someone
told them, Matthew.

417
00:39:30,627 --> 00:39:32,903
Think about it.
Someone you know.

418
00:39:32,964 --> 00:39:35,706
So you better ask yourself,
can you trust your landlord?

419
00:39:36,334 --> 00:39:37,608
Go ahead, you're not
going to get in my head.

420
00:39:37,669 --> 00:39:40,149
I already am
in your head.

421
00:39:40,204 --> 00:39:41,842
They're going to
isolate you, Matt.

422
00:39:41,906 --> 00:39:43,249
They're going to be real
nice to you at first.

423
00:39:43,308 --> 00:39:46,050
They're going to put their arm
around you and tell you things like,

424
00:39:46,111 --> 00:39:49,115
"You did a decent job, son.
We'll take it from here. "

425
00:39:49,181 --> 00:39:50,626
That's when you know
you're screwed.

426
00:39:52,085 --> 00:39:53,689
Forget about me. They're
going to focus on you.

427
00:39:53,753 --> 00:39:55,994
They're going to try and make a
connection between you and I.

428
00:39:56,589 --> 00:39:58,068
So that if this
all goes wrong,

429
00:39:58,124 --> 00:39:59,694
they'll have something
to fall back on

430
00:39:59,759 --> 00:40:02,171
in their little
Senate hearings.

431
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:08,002
I'm not your
only enemy tonight.

432
00:40:10,572 --> 00:40:12,051
So, it's someone in-house.

433
00:40:12,107 --> 00:40:14,314
It's the only way this
thing could've happened.

434
00:40:14,376 --> 00:40:16,014
We were
completely buttoned up.

435
00:40:17,879 --> 00:40:20,257
I want a list of everyone
who knew about this.

436
00:40:20,316 --> 00:40:21,818
Backgrounds, affiliations,

437
00:40:22,452 --> 00:40:24,523
particularly any
connections with Frost.

438
00:40:24,587 --> 00:40:27,158
Every movement right
up until this operation.

439
00:40:27,591 --> 00:40:29,867
Your extraction team, how
long had they been together?

440
00:40:30,861 --> 00:40:33,774
My team had been together
six months. Why?

441
00:40:34,431 --> 00:40:36,741
Well, I'm just trying to
get my head around this.

442
00:40:38,136 --> 00:40:39,274
That will do, thank you.

443
00:42:27,691 --> 00:42:29,034
Hello.
Hey.

444
00:42:29,826 --> 00:42:31,169
Baby, where are you?

445
00:42:31,228 --> 00:42:33,139
I'm all right.
I'm okay.

446
00:42:34,198 --> 00:42:35,233
I'm okay.

447
00:42:37,134 --> 00:42:39,774
I'm sorry I didn't call you
back, I saw your missed calls.

448
00:42:39,837 --> 00:42:41,510
You must be worried sick.

449
00:42:41,572 --> 00:42:42,846
Is everything okay?

450
00:42:43,675 --> 00:42:46,656
I'm good.
I'm good. Listen.

451
00:42:46,712 --> 00:42:48,350
This sounds so crazy.

452
00:42:48,714 --> 00:42:50,853
We had some threats against
the clinic last night,

453
00:42:50,916 --> 00:42:52,122
so Parker and I,
we stayed all night

454
00:42:52,184 --> 00:42:54,391
trying to get to
the bottom of it.

455
00:42:55,121 --> 00:42:58,364
And I'm sorry that I didn't cal! you back.
I should have, right away.

456
00:42:58,424 --> 00:42:59,960
I was so worried.

457
00:43:00,226 --> 00:43:01,569
I know.

458
00:43:04,265 --> 00:43:07,474
Can you do me a favor? Can you go
over to the window for a second?

459
00:43:07,534 --> 00:43:08,638
Why?

460
00:43:09,036 --> 00:43:11,175
Can you just take a quick
look out the window?

461
00:43:11,239 --> 00:43:13,310
I want you to see if
there's anyone out there.

462
00:43:13,375 --> 00:43:15,446
Are there any cars
that don't belong?

463
00:43:15,543 --> 00:43:17,352
Anyone hanging
around out front?

464
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,723
There's a police car.

465
00:43:22,919 --> 00:43:23,920
What's going on?

466
00:43:23,986 --> 00:43:25,021
I'm sorry about this.

467
00:43:25,087 --> 00:43:26,327
I know this is a lot,

468
00:43:26,389 --> 00:43:27,993
but we felt like
it would be best

469
00:43:28,057 --> 00:43:29,593
if we didn't go home
as a precaution,

470
00:43:29,660 --> 00:43:30,661
and I agree with him.

471
00:43:30,727 --> 00:43:32,468
I know there's nothing to worry
about, but I agree with him.

472
00:43:32,529 --> 00:43:34,839
I think you should just go to
Dena's for a little while,

473
00:43:34,898 --> 00:43:37,742
just for a few hours, and I'll
call you in a little bit.

474
00:43:39,504 --> 00:43:41,177
And we'll
get together, okay?

475
00:43:49,181 --> 00:43:50,285
Okay, I'll go.

476
00:43:54,486 --> 00:43:56,966
Okay. I love you. I'll talk
to you soon, all right?

477
00:43:57,023 --> 00:43:59,367
Don't worry. Okay, bye.

478
00:44:22,784 --> 00:44:24,491
She know what you do
for a living?

479
00:44:30,526 --> 00:44:33,996
The girl on the phone.
It was a girl, wasn't it?

480
00:44:35,399 --> 00:44:38,175
Maybe it was a guy,
I don't know.

481
00:44:38,268 --> 00:44:39,474
I don't judge.

482
00:44:44,876 --> 00:44:48,517
You can't expect to have a real
relationship in our line of work, Matthew.

483
00:44:51,317 --> 00:44:52,455
Don't worry. She's not
going to leave you.

484
00:44:52,518 --> 00:44:56,398
See, what happens is, you try
to protect her with lies,

485
00:44:56,455 --> 00:44:58,025
and then it starts
to add up.

486
00:45:00,327 --> 00:45:02,364
At the safe house you said that
they'd kill me to get to you.

487
00:45:02,429 --> 00:45:03,908
After awhile,
even the truth...

488
00:45:03,964 --> 00:45:06,240
Why?... starts to
sound like a lie.

489
00:45:07,534 --> 00:45:09,741
You have something. You got something
that they want. What is it?

490
00:45:09,804 --> 00:45:10,805
Is she a local?

491
00:45:10,872 --> 00:45:11,907
Don't worry about her.
What is it?

492
00:45:11,973 --> 00:45:13,475
Oh, it is a girl.

493
00:45:26,389 --> 00:45:29,927
You'll keep covering your
tracks, she'll keep believing.

494
00:45:29,993 --> 00:45:33,099
Because she wants to,
because she needs to.

495
00:45:34,731 --> 00:45:38,304
That's why we exist, you
and me, that's our job.

496
00:45:39,336 --> 00:45:40,974
To take advantage of that.

497
00:45:41,072 --> 00:45:45,179
People's desire
to believe.

498
00:45:45,844 --> 00:45:47,084
To trust.

499
00:45:56,989 --> 00:45:59,094
She's not going to
leave you, Matthew.

500
00:46:02,061 --> 00:46:03,802
You're going
to leave her.

501
00:46:10,304 --> 00:46:11,942
I'm not you.

502
00:46:28,224 --> 00:46:29,703
Correct, sir.
We verified it.

503
00:46:51,550 --> 00:46:54,190
That is your boy.
You take it.

504
00:46:57,223 --> 00:46:58,463
Everybody, stand by.

505
00:46:59,526 --> 00:47:01,130
Matty, it's me.

506
00:47:02,495 --> 00:47:03,496
How are you holding up?

507
00:47:04,898 --> 00:47:05,899
I'm all right.

508
00:47:10,137 --> 00:47:14,210
Matt, we can't get another
team in for at least 12 hours.

509
00:47:15,644 --> 00:47:16,714
Sorry.

