00:47:17,979 --> 00:47:20,687
We've cleared a new safe house
for you outside the city.

511
00:47:21,016 --> 00:47:22,495
There's a Go-Bag located

512
00:47:22,551 --> 00:47:27,296
at locker number 256, Green Point
Stadium Metrorail station.

513
00:47:27,557 --> 00:47:31,403
The combination
is 2-5-1-22.

514
00:47:31,460 --> 00:47:32,939
2-5-1-22.

515
00:47:32,995 --> 00:47:35,100
Now, the bag's
got a GPS in it.

516
00:47:35,165 --> 00:47:36,610
It'll direct you
to the safe house.

517
00:47:36,934 --> 00:47:39,778
But you got to be careful,
it's an active location.

518
00:47:39,836 --> 00:47:41,838
So, approach
with caution.

519
00:47:46,110 --> 00:47:47,145
Matt?

520
00:47:49,214 --> 00:47:52,354
Do you know how
they found Frost?

521
00:47:52,418 --> 00:47:53,795
Do you know who
led them to us?

522
00:47:56,855 --> 00:47:58,163
We're working on that.

523
00:47:59,091 --> 00:48:00,934
We're counting
on you, Matt.

524
00:48:01,294 --> 00:48:03,797
Get Frost to that safe house and
you can write your own ticket.

525
00:48:05,932 --> 00:48:07,206
I will.

526
00:48:09,837 --> 00:48:10,941
I will.

527
00:48:20,782 --> 00:48:21,920
Left at the light.

528
00:48:22,417 --> 00:48:24,363
To the stadium?

529
00:48:24,419 --> 00:48:25,625
Yeah.

530
00:48:49,481 --> 00:48:51,119
Hey, scarf.
How much for a scarf?

531
00:48:52,484 --> 00:48:53,792
Only fifty rand.

532
00:48:53,852 --> 00:48:54,990
Thanks.

533
00:48:57,523 --> 00:48:58,558
Cuff your hands
together.

534
00:48:58,624 --> 00:48:59,728
Together?
Yeah.

535
00:49:09,703 --> 00:49:10,704
Out.

536
00:49:15,376 --> 00:49:17,447
Are you sure you don't
want to just walk away from this?

537
00:49:17,512 --> 00:49:18,513
Can't do that.

538
00:49:18,579 --> 00:49:19,853
Yes, you can.
You should.

539
00:49:23,319 --> 00:49:26,493
Move. Go.
Across the street.

540
00:49:38,168 --> 00:49:42,173
Going to the game.
I like games.

541
00:49:42,406 --> 00:49:43,612
Metrorail,
straight ahead.

542
00:49:43,674 --> 00:49:44,675
Straight ahead.

543
00:49:54,753 --> 00:49:55,754
Right over there.

544
00:50:16,043 --> 00:50:17,044
Let's go.

545
00:50:40,704 --> 00:50:42,911
Help! Help! He's
trying to kidnap me!

546
00:50:42,973 --> 00:50:44,008
Whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa!

547
00:50:44,075 --> 00:50:46,351
He's trying to
kidnap me! Help!

548
00:50:46,411 --> 00:50:47,617
He's got a gun!

549
00:50:49,781 --> 00:50:51,920
He's got a gun! He's
got a gun right there!

550
00:50:53,519 --> 00:50:55,863
I'm undercover.
I'm undercover!

551
00:50:55,921 --> 00:50:58,094
Calm down, sir.
Everybody, calm down!

552
00:51:08,435 --> 00:51:09,937
Get down! Get down!

553
00:51:10,771 --> 00:51:13,411
All right! Okay!

554
00:51:30,326 --> 00:51:31,737
Get him up. Get up.

555
00:51:32,161 --> 00:51:33,299
Ow, ow, ow!

556
00:51:37,166 --> 00:51:41,205
I'm an American citizen. I don't
know what he wanted from me.

557
00:51:43,240 --> 00:51:44,378
Just calm down.

558
00:52:09,402 --> 00:52:12,008
Hey, hey, hey. I'm a police officer.
I'm from America.

559
00:52:12,072 --> 00:52:14,484
I arrested this man.
His name is Tobin Frost.

560
00:52:14,542 --> 00:52:15,714
Where did you take him?

561
00:52:15,776 --> 00:52:17,653
He's in the infirmary.

562
00:52:23,151 --> 00:52:24,858
There, there!
Is that it?

563
00:52:24,920 --> 00:52:28,834
Top left, second screen from the top!
Look, look, the infirmary.

564
00:52:32,127 --> 00:52:33,572
Right. Go back.

565
00:52:43,474 --> 00:52:45,613
Third-tier infirmary,
now! Move!

566
00:52:45,776 --> 00:52:47,653
Third-tier infirmary.
Go, now!

567
00:52:49,613 --> 00:52:50,614
Do you see?

568
00:53:23,464 --> 00:53:24,469
Don't move.

569
00:54:38,814 --> 00:54:39,853
Frost!

570
00:54:42,802 --> 00:54:43,807
Frost!

571
00:54:46,623 --> 00:54:47,662
Frost!

572
00:54:47,864 --> 00:54:48,938
Hey!

573
00:54:50,512 --> 00:54:51,929
Stop! Stop!

574
00:54:54,198 --> 00:54:55,341
Get out the way!

575
00:54:55,606 --> 00:54:56,680
Stop!

576
00:55:03,550 --> 00:55:04,761
No! Stop!

577
00:55:21,583 --> 00:55:22,617
Medic!

578
00:55:48,506 --> 00:55:49,677
Drop the gun.

579
00:55:50,475 --> 00:55:51,578
Drop it.

580
00:55:51,643 --> 00:55:53,485
I'm responsible for you.

581
00:55:57,181 --> 00:55:58,488
You're responsible
for yourself.

582
00:56:02,719 --> 00:56:03,856
Get on your knees.

583
00:56:15,764 --> 00:56:17,242
Are you going
to kill me?

584
00:56:29,442 --> 00:56:31,284
I only kill professionals.

585
00:56:50,828 --> 00:56:52,773
Height,
approximately six feet.

586
00:56:52,829 --> 00:56:55,468
Anglo, wearing
a stadium security jacket.

587
00:56:55,532 --> 00:56:58,808
The suspect was last seen entering
Green Point Stadium Metrorail,

588
00:56:58,869 --> 00:57:01,007
stadium concourse.

589
00:57:11,012 --> 00:57:13,651
Sir, we have a thread on what Frost
might be doing in Cape Town.

590
00:57:15,682 --> 00:57:17,183
Can you bring up...

591
00:57:18,352 --> 00:57:21,195
Alec Wade.
Fifteen-year NOC at MI6.

592
00:57:21,255 --> 00:57:24,531
Sabotage, counter-ambush,
counter-IED tactics,

593
00:57:24,590 --> 00:57:26,626
until he blew up an op
in Lisbon four years ago

594
00:57:26,692 --> 00:57:28,193
and was put on a desk,
pushing papers.

595
00:57:28,261 --> 00:57:30,501
Cape Town Police found him
shot through the head,

596
00:57:30,563 --> 00:57:33,441
high-powered rifle, 14
blocks from the consulate.

597
00:57:33,498 --> 00:57:35,841
Witnesses placed someone
fitting Frost's description

598
00:57:35,901 --> 00:57:37,402
in the car at the time
of the shooting.

599
00:57:37,469 --> 00:57:39,880
And we think, what? That
they were working together?

600
00:57:39,937 --> 00:57:42,849
They ran joint operations
in Hamburg in the mid-'80s.

601
00:57:43,207 --> 00:57:46,050
Frost's last sighting
was in Hamburg, 2011.

602
00:57:46,944 --> 00:57:48,547
And what are the Brits
saying about Wade?

603
00:57:48,611 --> 00:57:50,385
Officially,
they're saying nothing.

604
00:57:50,446 --> 00:57:51,480
Unofficially?

605
00:57:51,548 --> 00:57:53,823
He's been the subject of a
five-month internal investigation.

606
00:57:53,917 --> 00:57:55,589
They think he's
been trading intel.

607
00:57:55,652 --> 00:57:56,686
Hmm.

608
00:57:56,752 --> 00:57:58,890
So what the hell
did Wade leak to Frost

609
00:57:58,954 --> 00:58:02,127
that was so important it was
worth killing six of our men?

610
00:58:04,892 --> 00:58:09,237
I want more details from MI6.
Call in every chit you got.

611
00:58:09,297 --> 00:58:10,331
Yes, sir.

612
00:58:10,398 --> 00:58:12,741
David, I want
an internal investigation

613
00:58:12,799 --> 00:58:15,506
into Daniel Kiefer
and his team.

614
00:58:59,541 --> 00:59:01,679
I've got Weston calling in
for David Barlow.

615
00:59:05,679 --> 00:59:06,986
WESTON ON PHONE

616
00:59:07,047 --> 00:59:08,457
Frost?

617
00:59:08,515 --> 00:59:09,788
Yeah, he's gone.

618
00:59:10,350 --> 00:59:12,351
After I picked up the GPS,
he created a diversion,

619
00:59:12,418 --> 00:59:14,124
took out a couple of cops
at the stadium.

620
00:59:14,187 --> 00:59:15,563
Any idea
where he's headed?

621
00:59:15,622 --> 00:59:17,032
Not exactly,
but I will.

622
00:59:17,089 --> 00:59:19,466
This is Linklater. You
said he took out two cops?

623
00:59:19,524 --> 00:59:21,230
Matt, you're on speaker.

624
00:59:22,794 --> 00:59:25,706
Yes, ma'am.
At the Green Point Stadium.

625
00:59:25,763 --> 00:59:28,140
...involvement
in a possible kidnapping.

626
00:59:28,199 --> 00:59:31,179
The suspect is being described
as a white male of medium build.

627
00:59:31,235 --> 00:59:33,544
Stadium police is
reporting you shot a cop.

628
00:59:33,603 --> 00:59:35,673
I returned fire
in self-defense.

629
00:59:36,172 --> 00:59:38,674
The fact of the matter is,
Frost is on the loose.

630
00:59:38,875 --> 00:59:40,820
I've spent the last
14 hours with him.

631
00:59:40,877 --> 00:59:43,220
He might have said or done something
that could lead me to him.

632
00:59:43,279 --> 00:59:46,953
You are to stand down,
proceed to the consulate,

633
00:59:47,016 --> 00:59:49,325
and present yourself for exfil and debrief.
Acknowledge.

634
00:59:49,518 --> 00:59:51,861
By the time I'm debriefed,
Frost will be gone.

635
00:59:51,920 --> 00:59:53,421
I've spent 12
months researching

636
00:59:53,488 --> 00:59:54,693
every square inch
of this town.

637
00:59:54,756 --> 00:59:57,463
I will find Frost
and I'll deliver him.

638
00:59:57,525 --> 00:59:59,970
Weston, this is
Harlan Whitford, son.

639
01:00:02,963 --> 01:00:06,569
Now, you've done a fine job,
but we'll take it from here.

640
01:00:12,238 --> 01:00:13,545
Understood.

641
01:00:34,590 --> 01:00:35,693
Hello.

642
01:00:35,758 --> 01:00:37,168
Sir, I respectfully
request that,

643
01:00:37,226 --> 01:00:38,602
that exchange not
make it onto his files.

644
01:00:38,760 --> 01:00:41,137
He's either incompetent or he's
working with somebody else.

645
01:00:41,196 --> 01:00:42,697
Do not make this
about Weston.

646
01:00:42,864 --> 01:00:44,274
It was your guys
that lost Frost.

647
01:00:44,333 --> 01:00:46,039
It was your team that
folded at the safe house.

648
01:00:46,101 --> 01:00:49,240
I want both of you on an
airplane to Cape Town.

649
01:00:49,770 --> 01:00:53,945
Frost is trying to get out of the country.
Go find his ass.

650
01:01:26,103 --> 01:01:27,809
There you go, baby.

651
01:01:34,243 --> 01:01:35,653
One ticket to Jo'burg.

652
01:01:44,918 --> 01:01:45,918
Thank you.

653
01:02:20,984 --> 01:02:24,692
Police had detained
American NGO worker Matthew Weston

654
01:02:24,753 --> 01:02:27,494
as a possible suspect
in the shooting.

655
01:02:27,656 --> 01:02:30,226
Weston had been
detained earlier today,

656
01:02:30,292 --> 01:02:34,899
but managed to escape while being
questioned by stadium security officials

657
01:02:34,996 --> 01:02:37,566
about his involvement
in the shootings.

658
01:02:37,765 --> 01:02:41,234
The suspect has been described
as a white male of medium build,

659
01:02:41,301 --> 01:02:44,509
possibly wearing
a stadium security outfit.

660
01:02:49,241 --> 01:02:50,446
Baby

661
01:02:52,845 --> 01:02:54,255
Are you all right?

662
01:03:11,929 --> 01:03:13,430
I lied to you.

663
01:03:17,200 --> 01:03:19,338
About everything.
The NGO, Parker.

664
01:03:20,603 --> 01:03:21,603
My job.

665
01:03:23,171 --> 01:03:24,308
My family.

666
01:03:27,309 --> 01:03:29,310
So, who do you work for?

667
01:03:34,682 --> 01:03:35,887
The government.

668
01:03:38,718 --> 01:03:39,718
CIA.

669
01:03:40,019 --> 01:03:41,497
No, I don't...

670
01:03:42,489 --> 01:03:43,489
I don't do anything.

671
01:03:43,656 --> 01:03:47,660
I sit around in an apartment
all day I answer the phone.

672
01:04:00,638 --> 01:04:02,708
I need you to leave.

673
01:04:03,473 --> 01:04:06,419
I need you to do that
for me. Okay?

674
01:04:12,414 --> 01:04:13,448
Here.

675
01:04:15,584 --> 01:04:17,187
This is a ticket
to Jo'burg.

676
01:04:18,219 --> 01:04:19,561
When you get there, you go
straight to the airport.

677
01:04:19,621 --> 01:04:21,258
There's a 6:00 a.m. flight
to Paris.

678
01:04:22,056 --> 01:04:23,125
Take this.

679
01:04:23,758 --> 01:04:25,293
You take this.
If anyone stops you...

680
01:04:25,360 --> 01:04:28,238
If anyone stops you...
If anybody stops you...

681
01:04:28,295 --> 01:04:29,864
Who do you think I am?

682
01:04:29,930 --> 01:04:31,067
Stop, Stop

683
01:04:31,131 --> 01:04:32,165
Fuck you!

684
01:04:32,232 --> 01:04:34,973
Hey, stop. Stop it.

685
01:04:42,140 --> 01:04:46,019
We broke up a week ago. You
haven't seen me since, okay?

686
01:04:52,716 --> 01:04:53,921
I'm sorry.

687
01:05:00,456 --> 01:05:03,595
Just leave. Please?

688
01:05:07,629 --> 01:05:08,766
Do you love me?

689
01:05:08,830 --> 01:05:10,069
Very much.

690
01:05:11,233 --> 01:05:13,178
Go. Go.

691
01:05:19,807 --> 01:05:20,910
Go.

692
01:05:44,462 --> 01:05:46,771
Attention, all passengers,

693
01:05:46,831 --> 01:05:49,436
Platform 20
for Langa Township

694
01:05:49,499 --> 01:05:51,500
departing in five minutes.

695
01:05:53,637 --> 01:05:56,640
Langa Township,
departing in five minutes.

696
01:06:20,893 --> 01:06:24,101
Sir. Someone just logged into our
system using Weston's password

697
01:06:24,163 --> 01:06:26,335
accessing his
stored files.

698
01:06:27,699 --> 01:06:30,201
It's him. What
the hell is he doing?

699
01:06:31,003 --> 01:06:32,242
I'm not sure.

700
01:06:32,304 --> 01:06:33,543
I want to see
what he's looking at.

701
01:06:37,742 --> 01:06:38,913
He's pulled an old report

702
01:06:38,976 --> 01:06:42,320
on surveillance targets living
in the Langa Township area.

703
01:06:44,581 --> 01:06:48,221
It's a profile of Carlos
Villar, a Nicaraguan national.

704
01:06:48,351 --> 01:06:50,523
He's a known
document forger.

705
01:06:50,587 --> 01:06:52,463
Get me a copy
of Weston's report.

706
01:06:52,521 --> 01:06:53,590
Yes, sir.

707
01:06:54,323 --> 01:06:55,426
Logged off, sir.
He's gone.

708
01:06:55,891 --> 01:06:57,665
An Internet cafe
on Long Street.

709
01:07:25,250 --> 01:07:26,626
Like a black
Dorian Gray.

710
01:07:26,685 --> 01:07:28,789
That's right.
How you doing, brother?

711
01:07:30,021 --> 01:07:31,465
Come in.
Yes, sir.

712
01:07:36,960 --> 01:07:37,960
Illana?

713
01:07:38,729 --> 01:07:39,763
Hi.

714
01:07:39,830 --> 01:07:41,331
We have a guest.

715
01:07:43,132 --> 01:07:44,667
illana.
Good to meet you.

716
01:07:44,734 --> 01:07:46,337
Joseph, my daughter.

717
01:07:46,836 --> 01:07:48,746
How are you?
Hello.

718
01:07:48,804 --> 01:07:49,804
My son-in-law.

719
01:07:52,674 --> 01:07:54,209
May I offer you some tea?

720
01:07:54,743 --> 01:07:56,483
No, we're going
upstairs.

721
01:08:09,122 --> 01:08:10,600
I remembered.

722
01:08:12,692 --> 01:08:14,170
You even let it breathe.

723
01:08:19,131 --> 01:08:22,839
"Too long a sacrifice Can
make a stone of the heart

724
01:08:25,970 --> 01:08:28,176
"O when may it suffice?

725
01:08:29,207 --> 01:08:31,482
"That is Heaven's part"

726
01:08:36,380 --> 01:08:38,120
In the old days,
a cheap bottle

727
01:08:38,180 --> 01:08:40,216
of Flor de Cana kept us
happy all night.

728
01:08:40,483 --> 01:08:42,792
Mmm. Tastes change.

729
01:08:46,855 --> 01:08:48,356
People change.

730
01:08:53,495 --> 01:08:55,440
People don't change.

731
01:08:56,697 --> 01:08:58,471
We grow old.

732
01:08:58,532 --> 01:09:00,943
And some of us adapt.

733
01:09:02,268 --> 01:09:04,804
And learn how to enjoy
simple pleasures of life,

734
01:09:05,872 --> 01:09:09,045
like a family, a home.

735
01:09:09,776 --> 01:09:11,448
And for you...

736
01:09:11,977 --> 01:09:14,252
What's in that glass
right now, for you,

737
01:09:14,312 --> 01:09:16,723
is as good as it's
ever going to be.

738
01:09:19,316 --> 01:09:22,421
One day you'll understand.

739
01:09:22,486 --> 01:09:26,058
You got more past
than future, you learn.

740
01:09:28,291 --> 01:09:29,792
What is this?
An intervention?

741
01:09:35,631 --> 01:09:37,610
I thought you were dead.

742
01:09:52,145 --> 01:09:54,624
So, what brings you to my home
in the middle of the night

743
01:09:54,681 --> 01:09:56,159
after all these years?

744
01:10:10,762 --> 01:10:11,933
Ooh.

745
01:10:18,035 --> 01:10:19,069
Papa?

746
01:10:19,570 --> 01:10:20,604
Uh-huh.

747
01:10:20,671 --> 01:10:22,081
We're going.

748
01:10:22,539 --> 01:10:23,676
Okay, be careful.

749
01:10:23,739 --> 01:10:25,240
Okay, Papa

750
01:10:44,992 --> 01:10:46,800
What are you
going to do with this?

751
01:10:47,694 --> 01:10:49,673
Make some money.

752
01:10:49,929 --> 01:10:51,032
Let me borrow
your glasses.

753
01:10:58,537 --> 01:10:59,844
That's it. Listen.

754
01:10:59,905 --> 01:11:04,444
I'm going to need a new passport,
photo ID, driver's license,

755
01:11:04,509 --> 01:11:07,045
the whole shebang.
Can you do that for me?

756
01:11:08,212 --> 01:11:09,315
Yeah.

757
01:11:11,349 --> 01:11:12,383
You sure?

758
01:11:13,583 --> 01:11:14,652
Yes.

759
01:11:21,957 --> 01:11:23,993
Weston never
showed at the consulate.

760
01:11:24,059 --> 01:11:26,504
And he was just
accessing our secure server,

761
01:11:26,562 --> 01:11:29,371
searching for someone
to create an alias package.

762
01:11:31,132 --> 01:11:33,907
He's trying to
leave the country.

763
01:11:34,269 --> 01:11:36,111
Or he's going
after Frost.

764
01:11:37,070 --> 01:11:39,447
Look at what
happened at the soccer stadium.

765
01:11:39,973 --> 01:11:42,009
This guy
let Frost escape.

766
01:11:45,244 --> 01:11:47,223
I think Weston's turned.

767
01:11:47,280 --> 01:11:48,883
I know this boy.

768
01:11:49,549 --> 01:11:52,495
He's been looking for a
chance to prove himself.

769
01:11:52,551 --> 01:11:54,791
He's trying to
bring in Frost.

770
01:11:56,588 --> 01:11:57,930
Come on, David.

